she saw right through all that.

00:54.800 --> 00:57.633
Okay, what's going on?
You've been kinda bitchy all day.

00:57.890 --> 01:00.632
Excuse me?
I don't have a bitchy bone in my body.

01:02.270 --> 01:03.134
[chuckles]

01:04.520 --> 01:08.092
Okay, fine. There's a guy... at school.

01:08.440 --> 01:10.010
I love this story already. Who is he?

01:11.780 --> 01:13.645
He's... artsy.

01:13.860 --> 01:15.191
-Artsy.
-And dramatic.

01:15.280 --> 01:17.100
All code words for "too gay"?

01:17.200 --> 01:20.112
No, no, it's not that.
He's just totally not my type.

01:21.200 --> 01:22.690
Does this dramatic artist have a name?

01:24.000 --> 01:26.286
-Ryan Shaver.
-The guy with the 'zine?

01:26.370 --> 01:28.247
-Mm-hmm.
-[laughs]

01:28.330 --> 01:30.707
Holy shit.
Yeah, he's totally not your type.

01:30.790 --> 01:32.667
-Is he into you?
-Oh, yeah. No question.

01:32.750 --> 01:33.956
If you do say so yourself.

01:34.050 --> 01:38.589
Look, he's always smiling at me,
he laughs at jokes that are not jokes.

01:38.890 --> 01:40.710
And he, like, touches me
on the arm and shit.

01:41.300 --> 01:44.098
And what's the stimulus response
when he touches you on the arm?

01:44.180 --> 01:46.671
Part of me wants to say,
"Watch the leather, homo."

01:47.640 --> 01:50.108
Other part of me wants to throw him
against the locker and kiss him.

01:51.730 --> 01:52.560
[laughing]

01:52.650 --> 01:55.187
Oh, dear Lord. You are in trouble.

01:55.570 --> 01:57.060
-Yeah.
-You have to ask him out.

01:57.150 --> 01:58.481
-Ah, no.
-Come on.

01:58.780 --> 02:01.066
You need to restore my faith
in teenage male-kind.

02:01.530 --> 02:04.863
-Well, not all of us are Justin Foley.
-Prove it.

02:08.160 --> 02:10.208
[Tony] She was the kind of friend
who challenged me,

02:10.290 --> 02:11.575
whether I liked it or not.

02:11.960 --> 02:14.201
Hannah and I had a relationship like...

02:15.630 --> 02:17.461
well, we kept each other's secrets.

02:20.050 --> 02:21.540
So, what do you know

02:21.970 --> 02:24.461
that someone _
doesn't want you saying In court?

02:26.470 --> 02:27.346
I know a lot.

02:30.480 --> 02:31.469
I've done a lot.

02:32.020 --> 02:33.180
But you can't tell the cops?

02:34.610 --> 02:36.931
-Or your folks?
-Nope.

02:37.570 --> 02:41.939
-So, how bad is it gonna be?
-The school called me in, not the Bakers.

02:42.620 --> 02:43.826
The school wants me to talk

02:43.910 --> 02:47.823
about how Hannah blamed lots of people
and wanted revenge.

02:47.910 --> 02:51.289
-They told you that?
-No. The Bakers' lawyer did.

02:52.670 --> 02:55.878
He also warned me he would
have to make me look unreliable.

02:55.960 --> 02:59.669
-Oh, shit.
-I could fuck everything up.

03:01.260 --> 03:05.924
-For the Bakers?
-Yeah, for the Bakers, for my family.

03:10.520 --> 03:11.339
For us.

03:13.560 --> 03:15.687
Oh, so... we're an "us" now?

03:18.740 --> 03:20.139
I mean, yeah, like...

03:22.610 --> 03:25.443
-until I fuck it up.
-Oh, you won't.

03:27.450 --> 03:28.280
Not us.

03:39.710 --> 03:43.498
[Clay] Look, don't you get it?
It has to be the Clubhouse.

03:44.890 --> 03:45.709
Right.

03:47.470 --> 03:49.267
-Are you high?
-Jesus.

03:50.430 --> 03:51.306
No.

03:51.390 --> 03:53.642
-I can't bring that shit home again.
-I'm not.

03:55.690 --> 03:56.600
I'm just tired.

03:58.150 --> 04:01.734
So, if you weren't using, what have you
been doing the past 48 hours?

04:02.070 --> 04:03.981
-I saw my mom.
-Your mom?

04:04.360 --> 04:06.021
I thought you didn't know where she moved.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.940
Well, turns out I lie sometimes.

04:08.660 --> 04:11.993
-Wait, so you went home?
-No, I saw my mom.

04:16.080 --> 04:17.411
She gave me some cash.

04:18.710 --> 04:23.579
-She gave you that?
-Here. It's for you. Consider it rent.

04:23.970 --> 04:28.043
-Till I can find something permanent.
-Keep it. I don't pay rent anyway. So...

04:29.720 --> 04:33.304
If you have all that cash...
why'd you call me?

04:34.980 --> 04:36.049
You said you needed me.

04:39.610 --> 04:43.239
I'm just-- I'm done
with doing fucked-up things.

04:45.490 --> 04:46.946
[sighs] Yeah.

04:48.990 --> 04:51.447
I may need you to do
one or two more fucked-up things.

04:55.120 --> 04:56.860
[shower running]

04:59.090 --> 05:04.255
[Tony] Me, I try to be a good friend...
in the way I know how.

05:08.300 --> 05:09.289
[door creaks]

05:10.970 --> 05:11.800
[door closes]

05:16.140 --> 05:17.095
He came back.

05:18.900 --> 05:19.764
Yeah.

05:20.770 --> 05:23.068
Eventually, you have to stop running,
I guess.

05:24.740 --> 05:26.776
I'm sorry... about the other night.

05:28.070 --> 05:29.776
You didn't say anything I didn't deserve.

05:47.970 --> 05:49.676
I'm angry all the time, Hannah.

05:52.100 --> 05:53.636
